postcontent:
Harrington and Richardson H&R "Gunfighter" 660 Double Action Revolver . $219 O.N.O. 

6 shot .22 Long / long rifle, 5 1/2" Barrel, Excellent bore. Aout 96% Original Blue Showing virtually no wear with only a few cylinder drag marks and a small holster wear spot at the end of the ejection rod tube. Action works excellent (both single and double action) The serial number puts the gun at about a 1959 manufacture. Very shootable and very accurate. Put some CB caps in this and be real quiet, LOL. Come to me and I will even throw in a hard case.

Sorry, I don't have the original box and papers. Gun is in good fireable shape. It has been in the safe for many years only to be pulled and cleaned and inspected. Look at my other ads also. I will be selling the bulk of my collection over the next month or so to fund a large project. I will have some things for sale that will interest all different collectors and shooters.

 Sales Order:

If the ad is up and I do not list it as "sale pending" then it is still for sale. Do not message me with "do you still have it" or "is it still available". I will assume you are a spam bot trying to get my email address and I will ignore you. "I am interested" is a close second that is being used also. I myself answer an ad with where I am located and when I would be available. That always gets a persons attention. I try to sell to the first person who contacts me first. After that I contact the second response and so on. This had always worked for me in the past, but as time changed and more people flaked on me or wanted me to wait beyond an agreed upon time/day, I have changed my method to a "first with the cash gets the prize". As in everything communication is king, I can't read your mind. I am not interested in Shipping a gun anywhere. If I was, I would be advertising it to a national audience auction site and asking more. Like all things, If I get enough ridiculous offers and somebody just has to have this because it reminds them of the one dear old dad used to have and has more dollars than the local's sense, I will ship to your local FFL if he will accept a direct ship gun from a private owner. Postal Money order to be cleared first. I will not sell to a low baller, I will sell through afore mentioned Auction site or just keep the item.

Disclaimers and Information:

 I am not a gun shop, there is no sales tax or background fees. I do not take credit cards. I also will not accept a cashier's check, personal check, money order or anything other than CASH. If you email me a low-ball offer and say that you will pay in CASH, like it is something special and I am selling a used car, I will assume you are a effing retard who shouldn't own a gun to begin with. Contact me and I will email the best pictures I can manage. No, I am not a professional photographer. I do not look at my phone all day hoping I have email. I check it when I get home from work and occasionally on the week ends. Please don't get discouraged and think I am ignoring you if I don't return an email in 5 minutes. I am not willing to drive across the state to meet you so that you can inspect the gun and make me an offer. Driving halfway across town is a different matter all together, but I hope you will have made your offer ahead of time. If not, I may take my toys and go home. Yes, I know what the asking price on Gunbroker is, I also know what they sell for along with shipping and transfer fee and credit card fee. I do not dignify ridiculous offers with a reasonable response, they will get a ridiculous response, if any response at all. I do not NEED to sell anything, I would just LIKE to. Reasonable offers are considered, not necessarily accepted, but considered. Please do not drag the moral character of my relatives into any disagreement, I can't help it, they are like that. Mom in particular. All firearms should be considered loaded at all times, they may not be, but it is safer to consider them that way. Spammers and scammers beware, I have a loaded LOIC (low orbit ion cannon) and I know how to use it.

P.S.

I am sorry this is sooo long but every day somebody fails to see reason and acts outside the bounds of my endurance. Check back often as the list continues to grow, ha.

title: For Sale:  COLT GOVERNMENT 1911 COMMERCIAL - 1933
postcontent:
A few years ago, I purchased this Colt Government Commercial from a semi-retired dealer in upstate New York.  He had it on consignment from the estate of an insurance executive who had recently passed-away. One of the heirs advised him that their father had purchased the gun “several years ago” and kept it in the safe in his home office.

The dealer was under the impression that the Colt had been manufactured in 1933 and was, at one time, in South America.  I bought the gun simply on the basis that I thought it was beautiful.

I took it out and ran it through its paces, finding that it shot very reliably and true to aim, consistently. It particularly liked cheap, Winchester white box fmj ball ammo.  

I conducted some research about its origin. The C168004 serial number indicates that it is one of the 5,320 Hartford Colts that were made in 1933 and issued to the Buenos Aires Police Department, aka a “Policia de la Capital” pistol. This was confirmed by the “No. 1849” stock number stamped on the top of the slide. The “JLD” stamp by the mag release further indicates a South American presence at one time. The unusual thing about the pistol is the absence of any of the Argentine roll marks customarily found on these pistols. 

As you can see from the pictures, condition is excellent. I assume that it was professionally refinished, however the Colt roll-marks look as fresh and sharp as they do on some of my Colt originals. I also assume that the grips are replacements, as they are unblemished and the checkering is still sharp. The gun is mechanically excellent. The two identical magazines are generic aftermarket.

It will be a long time before you find another pure-blooded Colt from the 1930s in this condition for the price offered.
